Reasoning: The paper deals with data structures for representing Boolean functions, specifically reduced ordered binary decision diagrams (BDDs) and zero-suppressed binary decision diagrams (ZDDs). This falls under the category of data structures (cs.DS) and discrete mathematics (cs.DM). The paper also discusses algorithms for operating on these data structures, which could fall under the category of algorithms and complexity (cs.CC). The use of these data structures for encoding word lists and solving combinatorial problems suggests a connection to logic and computation (cs.LO) and programming languages (cs.PL).
